Architect Captain Charles Clarke of Troon, Scotland, blended unusual elevation changes of more than 85-feet with features of traditional golf design. Rolling fairways (some dramatic), undulating greens and well-placed berms, bunkers and sandy waste areas, as well as water on 11 holes all only begin to characterize the aura of El Campeon. Rated 4 stars by Golf Digest's "Best Places To Play, 2008/2009." You can't miss the Spanish-style resort inn/ hotel in the background. 'Championship Golf' at Mission Inn... always a challenge, always a memorable experience. An easy 35-40 minute drive from most Orlando areas; well worth the drive!
